23
00:01:21,060 --> 00:01:23,500
So that's kind of obvious.

24
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,780
There's a right-hand rule.

25
00:01:24,780 --> 00:01:27,820
If the system is rotating about an axis,

26
00:01:27,820 --> 00:01:31,200
you don't know offhand, without a definition,

27
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,880
whether the angular momentum is

28
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:34,560
pointing that way or that way.

29
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:36,860
All I told you was along the axis.

30
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:38,060
So you need a rule.

31
00:01:38,060 --> 00:01:39,400
The rule is the right-hand rule.

32
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:41,440
If it's rotating that way, you wrap your fingers

33
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:44,340
